# demand_neighborhood_witness -- oracle input batches (the SAME add_edge stream
# the driver sends). BIRTH phase: two edge epochs. R-a2 REBUILD phase: four
# single-edge epochs (each a post-demand edge in the driver). The oracle
# evaluates the plain (undemanded) program, so its neighborhood rows are the
# FULL single-hop relation -- the answer-identity referee for the demand-ON
# driver's per-key answers (demand-blind, so it gains all four rebuild rows
# including the undemanded (13,14)).
#
# Batch 1: 1's first two out-edges, the 9->9 self-loop, the detached 7->8.
batch
+ add_edge 1 2
+ add_edge 1 3
+ add_edge 9 9
+ add_edge 7 8
end
# Batch 2: 1's third out-edge and 3's out-edges (out-of-neighborhood for key 1).
batch
+ add_edge 1 4
+ add_edge 3 5
+ add_edge 3 6
end
# R-a2 REBUILD epochs: one post-demand edge each (matches the driver's REBUILD
# phase). (13,14) is an UNDEMANDED-key edge — demand-blind, so the oracle sees it.
batch
+ add_edge 1 11
end
batch
+ add_edge 3 7
end
batch
+ add_edge 5 12
end
batch
+ add_edge 13 14
end
